   I add limitation to thread pool to avoid backlog. 
```
  ZipkinHbaseStorageAutoConfiguration
  @Bean
  @ConditionalOnMissingBean(Executor.class)
  Executor executor() {
    ThreadPoolTaskExecutor executor = new ThreadPoolTaskExecutor();
    executor.setThreadNamePrefix("ZipkinHbaseStorage-");
    executor.setCorePoolSize(20); // add limitation
    executor.setMaxPoolSize(20); // add limitation
    executor.initialize();
    return executor.getThreadPoolExecutor();// change return value
  }
```

```
InternalBlockingToAsyncSpanConsumerAdapter
@Override public void accept(final List<Span> spans, Callback<Void> callback) {
    ThreadPoolExecutor t = (ThreadPoolExecutor) executor;
    while (t.getQueue().size() >= 20) { // add condition
      try {
        Thread.sleep(3000);
      } catch (InterruptedException e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
      }
    }
    executor.execute(new InternalCallbackRunnable<Void>(callback) {
      @Override
      Void complete() {
        delegate.accept(spans);
        return null;
      }

      @Override
      public String toString() {
        return "Accept(" + spans + ")";
      }
    });
  }
```
